36template <ARM::ISAKind ISAKind>
37std::string FormatExtensionFlags(uint64_t Flags) {
38 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
39
40 if (ISAKind == ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64) {
41 // AEK_NONE is not meant to be shown to the user so the target parser
42 // does not recognise it. It is relevant here though.
43 if (Flags & AArch64::AEK_NONE)
44 Features.push_back("none");
45 AArch64::getExtensionFeatures(Flags, Features);
46 } else {
47 if (Flags & ARM::AEK_NONE)
48 Features.push_back("none");
49 ARM::getExtensionFeatures(Flags, Features);
50 }
51
52 // The target parser also includes every extension you don't have.
53 // E.g. if AEK_CRC is not set then it adds "-crc". Not useful here.
54 Features.erase(std::remove_if(Features.begin(), Features.end(),
55 [](StringRef extension) {
56 return extension.startswith("-");
57 }),
58 Features.end());
59
60 return llvm::join(Features, ", ");
61}
62
63template <ARM::ISAKind ISAKind>
64testing::AssertionResult
65AssertSameExtensionFlags(const char *m_expr, const char *n_expr,
66 uint64_t ExpectedFlags, uint64_t GotFlags) {
67 if (ExpectedFlags == GotFlags)
68 return testing::AssertionSuccess();
69
70 return testing::AssertionFailure() << llvm::formatv(
71 "Expected extension flags: {0} ({1:x})\n"
72 " Got extension flags: {2} ({3:x})\n",
73 FormatExtensionFlags<ISAKind>(ExpectedFlags), ExpectedFlags,
74 FormatExtensionFlags<ISAKind>(GotFlags), GotFlags);
75}
76
77struct ARMCPUTestParams {
78 ARMCPUTestParams(StringRef CPUName, StringRef ExpectedArch,
79 StringRef ExpectedFPU, uint64_t ExpectedFlags,
80 StringRef CPUAttr)
81 : CPUName(CPUName), ExpectedArch(ExpectedArch), ExpectedFPU(ExpectedFPU),
82 ExpectedFlags(ExpectedFlags), CPUAttr(CPUAttr) {}
83
84 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &os,
85 const ARMCPUTestParams &params) {
86 return os << "\"" << params.CPUName.str() << "\", \""
87 << params.ExpectedArch.str() << "\", \""
88 << params.ExpectedFPU.str() << "\", 0x" << std::hex
89 << params.ExpectedFlags << ", \"" << params.CPUAttr.str() << "\"";
90 }
91
92 StringRef CPUName;
93 StringRef ExpectedArch;
94 StringRef ExpectedFPU;
95 uint64_t ExpectedFlags;
96 StringRef CPUAttr;
97};
98
99class ARMCPUTestFixture : public ::testing::TestWithParam<ARMCPUTestParams> {};
100
101TEST_P(ARMCPUTestFixture, ARMCPUTests) {
102 auto params = GetParam();
103
104 ARM::ArchKind AK = ARM::parseCPUArch(params.CPUName);
105 EXPECT_EQ(params.ExpectedArch, ARM::getArchName(AK));
106
107 unsigned FPUKind = ARM::getDefaultFPU(params.CPUName, AK);
108 EXPECT_EQ(params.ExpectedFPU, ARM::getFPUName(FPUKind));
109
110 uint64_t default_extensions = ARM::getDefaultExtensions(params.CPUName, AK);
111 EXPECT_PRED_FORMAT2(AssertSameExtensionFlags<ARM::ISAKind::ARM>,
112 params.ExpectedFlags, default_extensions);
113
114 EXPECT_EQ(params.CPUAttr, ARM::getCPUAttr(AK));
115}

119// of the default extensions for its architecture and for the CPU.
120// So if a CPU has no extra extensions, it adds AEK_NONE.

386 ARM::AEK_FP | ARM::AEK_RAS | ARM::AEK_LOB |
387 ARM::AEK_FP16,
388 "8.1-M.Mainline"),
389 ARMCPUTestParams("iwmmxt", "iwmmxt", "none", ARM::AEK_NONE, "iwmmxt"),
390 ARMCPUTestParams("xscale", "xscale", "none", ARM::AEK_NONE, "xscale"),
391 ARMCPUTestParams("swift", "armv7s", "neon-vfpv4",
392 ARM::AEK_HWDIVARM | ARM::AEK_HWDIVTHUMB | ARM::AEK_DSP,
393 "7-S")), );

395static constexpr unsigned NumARMCPUArchs = 92;

397TEST(TargetParserTest, testARMCPUArchList) {
398 SmallVector<StringRef, NumARMCPUArchs> List;
399 ARM::fillValidCPUArchList(List);
400
401 // No list exists for these in this test suite, so ensure all are
402 // valid, and match the expected 'magic' count.
403 EXPECT_EQ(List.size(), NumARMCPUArchs);
404 for(StringRef CPU : List) {
405 EXPECT_NE(ARM::parseCPUArch(CPU), ARM::ArchKind::INVALID);
406 }
407}

409TEST(TargetParserTest, testInvalidARMArch) {
410 auto InvalidArchStrings = {"armv", "armv99", "noarm"};
411 for (const char* InvalidArch : InvalidArchStrings)
412 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::parseArch(InvalidArch), ARM::ArchKind::INVALID);
413}

415bool testARMArch(StringRef Arch, StringRef DefaultCPU, StringRef SubArch,
416 unsigned ArchAttr) {
417 ARM::ArchKind AK = ARM::parseArch(Arch);
418 bool Result = (AK != ARM::ArchKind::INVALID);
419 Result &= ARM::getDefaultCPU(Arch).equals(DefaultCPU);
420 Result &= ARM::getSubArch(AK).equals(SubArch);
421 Result &= (ARM::getArchAttr(AK) == ArchAttr);
422 return Result;
423}

629TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMFPUVersion) {
630 for (ARM::FPUKind FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(0);
631 FK <= ARM::FPUKind::FK_LAST;
632 FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(static_cast<unsigned>(FK) + 1))
633 if (FK == ARM::FK_LAST || ARM::getFPUName(FK) == "invalid" ||
634 ARM::getFPUName(FK) == "none" || ARM::getFPUName(FK) == "softvfp")
635 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::FPUVersion::NONE, ARM::getFPUVersion(FK));
636 else
637 EXPECT_NE(ARM::FPUVersion::NONE, ARM::getFPUVersion(FK));
638}
639
640TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMFPUNeonSupportLevel) {
641 for (ARM::FPUKind FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(0);
642 FK <= ARM::FPUKind::FK_LAST;
643 FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(static_cast<unsigned>(FK) + 1))
644 if (FK == ARM::FK_LAST ||
645 ARM::getFPUName(FK).find("neon") == std::string::npos)
646 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::NeonSupportLevel::None,
647 ARM::getFPUNeonSupportLevel(FK));
648 else
649 EXPECT_NE(ARM::NeonSupportLevel::None,
650 ARM::getFPUNeonSupportLevel(FK));
651}
652
653TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMFPURestriction) {
654 for (ARM::FPUKind FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(0);
655 FK <= ARM::FPUKind::FK_LAST;
656 FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(static_cast<unsigned>(FK) + 1)) {
657 if (FK == ARM::FK_LAST ||
658 (ARM::getFPUName(FK).find("d16") == std::string::npos &&
659 ARM::getFPUName(FK).find("vfpv3xd") == std::string::npos))
660 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::FPURestriction::None, ARM::getFPURestriction(FK));
661 else
662 EXPECT_NE(ARM::FPURestriction::None, ARM::getFPURestriction(FK));
663 }
664}

666TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMExtensionFeatures) {
667 std::map<uint64_t, std::vector<StringRef>> Extensions;
668
669 for (auto &Ext : ARM::ARCHExtNames) {
670 if (Ext.Feature && Ext.NegFeature)
671 Extensions[Ext.ID] = { StringRef(Ext.Feature),
672 StringRef(Ext.NegFeature) };
673 }
674
675 Extensions[ARM::AEK_HWDIVARM] = { "+hwdiv-arm", "-hwdiv-arm" };
676 Extensions[ARM::AEK_HWDIVTHUMB] = { "+hwdiv", "-hwdiv" };
677
678 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
679
680 EXPECT_FALSE(ARM::getExtensionFeatures(ARM::AEK_INVALID, Features));
681
682 for (auto &E : Extensions) {
683 // test +extension
684 Features.clear();
685 ARM::getExtensionFeatures(E.first, Features);
686 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, E.second.at(0)));
687 EXPECT_TRUE(Extensions.size() == Features.size());
688
689 // test -extension
690 Features.clear();
691 ARM::getExtensionFeatures(~E.first, Features);
692 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, E.second.at(1)));
693 EXPECT_TRUE(Extensions.size() == Features.size());
694 }
695}

697TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMFPUFeatures) {
698 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
699 for (ARM::FPUKind FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(0);
700 FK <= ARM::FPUKind::FK_LAST;
701 FK = static_cast<ARM::FPUKind>(static_cast<unsigned>(FK) + 1))
702 EXPECT_TRUE((FK == ARM::FK_INVALID || FK >= ARM::FK_LAST)
703 ? !ARM::getFPUFeatures(FK, Features)
704 : ARM::getFPUFeatures(FK, Features));
705}

736
737static bool
738testArchExtDependency(const char *ArchExt,
739 const std::initializer_list<const char *> &Expected) {
740 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
741 unsigned FPUID;
742
743 if (!ARM::appendArchExtFeatures("", ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_1MMainline, ArchExt,
744 Features, FPUID))
745 return false;
746
747 return llvm::all_of(Expected, [&](StringRef Ext) {
748 return llvm::is_contained(Features, Ext);
749 });
750}
751
752TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMArchExtDependencies) {
753 EXPECT_TRUE(testArchExtDependency("mve", {"+mve", "+dsp"}));
754 EXPECT_TRUE(testArchExtDependency("mve.fp", {"+mve.fp", "+mve", "+dsp"}));
755 EXPECT_TRUE(testArchExtDependency("nodsp", {"-dsp", "-mve", "-mve.fp"}));
756 EXPECT_TRUE(testArchExtDependency("nomve", {"-mve", "-mve.fp"}));
757}

766TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMparseArchEndianAndISA) {
767 const char *Arch[] = {
768 "v2", "v2a", "v3", "v3m", "v4", "v4t", "v5", "v5t",
769 "v5e", "v5te", "v5tej", "v6", "v6j", "v6k", "v6hl", "v6t2",
770 "v6kz", "v6z", "v6zk", "v6-m", "v6m", "v6sm", "v6s-m", "v7-a",
771 "v7", "v7a", "v7ve", "v7hl", "v7l", "v7-r", "v7r", "v7-m",
772 "v7m", "v7k", "v7s", "v7e-m", "v7em", "v8-a", "v8", "v8a",
773 "v8l", "v8.1-a", "v8.1a", "v8.2-a", "v8.2a", "v8.3-a", "v8.3a", "v8.4-a",
774 "v8.4a", "v8.5-a","v8.5a", "v8.6-a", "v8.6a", "v8.7-a", "v8.7a", "v8-r",
775 "v8m.base", "v8m.main", "v8.1m.main"
776 };
777
778 for (unsigned i = 0; i < array_lengthof(Arch); i++) {
779 std::string arm_1 = "armeb" + (std::string)(Arch[i]);
780 std::string arm_2 = "arm" + (std::string)(Arch[i]) + "eb";
781 std::string arm_3 = "arm" + (std::string)(Arch[i]);
782 std::string thumb_1 = "thumbeb" + (std::string)(Arch[i]);
783 std::string thumb_2 = "thumb" + (std::string)(Arch[i]) + "eb";
784 std::string thumb_3 = "thumb" + (std::string)(Arch[i]);
785
786 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::BIG, ARM::parseArchEndian(arm_1));
787 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::BIG, ARM::parseArchEndian(arm_2));
788 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::LITTLE, ARM::parseArchEndian(arm_3));
789
790 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::ARM, ARM::parseArchISA(arm_1));
791 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::ARM, ARM::parseArchISA(arm_2));
792 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::ARM, ARM::parseArchISA(arm_3));
793 if (i >= 4) {
794 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::BIG, ARM::parseArchEndian(thumb_1));
795 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::BIG, ARM::parseArchEndian(thumb_2));
796 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::LITTLE, ARM::parseArchEndian(thumb_3));
797
798 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::THUMB, ARM::parseArchISA(thumb_1));
799 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::THUMB, ARM::parseArchISA(thumb_2));
800 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::THUMB, ARM::parseArchISA(thumb_3));
801 }
802 }
803
804 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::LITTLE, ARM::parseArchEndian("aarch64"));
805 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::LITTLE, ARM::parseArchEndian("arm64_32"));
806 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::EndianKind::BIG, ARM::parseArchEndian("aarch64_be"));
807
808 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("aarch64"));
809 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("aarch64_be"));
810 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("arm64"));
811 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("arm64_be"));
812 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("arm64_32"));
813 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64, ARM::parseArchISA("aarch64_32"));
814}

816TEST(TargetParserTest, ARMparseArchProfile) {
817 for (unsigned i = 0; i < array_lengthof(ARMArch); i++) {
818 switch (ARM::parseArch(ARMArch[i])) {
819 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV6M:
820 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7M:
821 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7EM:
822 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8MMainline:
823 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8MBaseline:
824 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_1MMainline:
825 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ProfileKind::M, ARM::parseArchProfile(ARMArch[i]));
826 break;
827 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7R:
828 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8R:
829 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ProfileKind::R, ARM::parseArchProfile(ARMArch[i]));
830 break;
831 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7A:
832 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7VE:
833 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV7K:
834 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8A:
835 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_1A:
836 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_2A:
837 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_3A:
838 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_4A:
839 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_5A:
840 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_6A:
841 case ARM::ArchKind::ARMV8_7A:
842 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ProfileKind::A, ARM::parseArchProfile(ARMArch[i]));
843 break;
844 default:
845 EXPECT_EQ(ARM::ProfileKind::INVALID, ARM::parseArchProfile(ARMArch[i]));
846 break;
847 }
848 }
849}

857}

859class AArch64CPUTestFixture
860 : public ::testing::TestWithParam<ARMCPUTestParams> {};
861
862TEST_P(AArch64CPUTestFixture, testAArch64CPU) {
863 ARMCPUTestParams params = GetParam();
864
865 AArch64::ArchKind AK = AArch64::parseCPUArch(params.CPUName);
866 EXPECT_EQ(params.ExpectedArch, AArch64::getArchName(AK));
867
868 uint64_t default_extensions =
869 AArch64::getDefaultExtensions(params.CPUName, AK);
870 EXPECT_PRED_FORMAT2(AssertSameExtensionFlags<ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64>,
871 params.ExpectedFlags, default_extensions);
872
873 unsigned FPUKind = AArch64::getDefaultFPU(params.CPUName, AK);
874 EXPECT_EQ(params.ExpectedFPU, ARM::getFPUName(FPUKind));
875
876 EXPECT_EQ(params.CPUAttr, AArch64::getCPUAttr(AK));
877}

1177static constexpr unsigned NumAArch64CPUArchs = 47;
1178
1179TEST(TargetParserTest, testAArch64CPUArchList) {
1180 SmallVector<StringRef, NumAArch64CPUArchs> List;
1181 AArch64::fillValidCPUArchList(List);
1182
1183 // No list exists for these in this test suite, so ensure all are
1184 // valid, and match the expected 'magic' count.
1185 EXPECT_EQ(List.size(), NumAArch64CPUArchs);
1186 for(StringRef CPU : List) {
1187 EXPECT_NE(AArch64::parseCPUArch(CPU), AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID);
1188 }
1189}
1190
1191bool testAArch64Arch(StringRef Arch, StringRef DefaultCPU, StringRef SubArch,
1192 unsigned ArchAttr) {
1193 AArch64::ArchKind AK = AArch64::parseArch(Arch);
1194 return (AK != AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID) &
1195 AArch64::getDefaultCPU(Arch).equals(DefaultCPU) &
1196 AArch64::getSubArch(AK).equals(SubArch) &
1197 (AArch64::getArchAttr(AK) == ArchAttr);
1198}
1199
1200TEST(TargetParserTest, testAArch64Arch) {
1201 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8-a", "cortex-a53", "v8",
1202 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1203 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.1-a", "generic", "v8.1a",
1204 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1205 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.2-a", "generic", "v8.2a",
1206 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1207 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.3-a", "generic", "v8.3a",
1208 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1209 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.4-a", "generic", "v8.4a",
1210 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1211 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.5-a", "generic", "v8.5a",
1212 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1213 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.6-a", "generic", "v8.6a",
1214 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1215 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Arch("armv8.7-a", "generic", "v8.7a",
1216 ARMBuildAttrs::CPUArch::v8_A));
1217}
1218
1219bool testAArch64Extension(StringRef CPUName, AArch64::ArchKind AK,
1220 StringRef ArchExt) {
1221 return AArch64::getDefaultExtensions(CPUName, AK) &
1222 AArch64::parseArchExt(ArchExt);
1223}
1224
1225TEST(TargetParserTest, testAArch64Extension) {
1226 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a34",
1227 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));
1228 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a35",
1229 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));
1230 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a53",
1231 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));
1232 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a55",
1233 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));
1234 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a55",
1235 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "fp16"));
1236 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a55",
1237 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "fp16fml"));
1238 EXPECT_TRUE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a55",
1239 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "dotprod"));
1240 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a57",
1241 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));
1242 EXPECT_FALSE(testAArch64Extension("cortex-a72",
1243 AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID, "ras"));

1363TEST(TargetParserTest, AArch64ExtensionFeatures) {
1364 std::vector<uint64_t> Extensions = {
1365 AArch64::AEK_CRC, AArch64::AEK_CRYPTO,
1366 AArch64::AEK_FP, AArch64::AEK_SIMD,
1367 AArch64::AEK_FP16, AArch64::AEK_PROFILE,
1368 AArch64::AEK_RAS, AArch64::AEK_LSE,
1369 AArch64::AEK_RDM, AArch64::AEK_DOTPROD,
1370 AArch64::AEK_SVE, AArch64::AEK_SVE2,
1371 AArch64::AEK_SVE2AES, AArch64::AEK_SVE2SM4,
1372 AArch64::AEK_SVE2SHA3, AArch64::AEK_SVE2BITPERM,
1373 AArch64::AEK_RCPC, AArch64::AEK_FP16FML };
1374
1375 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
1376
1377 uint64_t ExtVal = 0;
1378 for (auto Ext : Extensions)
1379 ExtVal |= Ext;
1380
1381 EXPECT_FALSE(AArch64::getExtensionFeatures(AArch64::AEK_INVALID, Features));
1382 EXPECT_TRUE(!Features.size());
1383
1384 AArch64::getExtensionFeatures(ExtVal, Features);
1385 EXPECT_TRUE(Extensions.size() == Features.size());
1386
1387 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+crc"));
1388 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+crypto"));
1389 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+fp-armv8"));
1390 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+neon"));
1391 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+fullfp16"));
1392 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+spe"));
1393 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+ras"));
1394 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+lse"));
1395 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+rdm"));
1396 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+dotprod"));
1397 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+rcpc"));
1398 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+fp16fml"));
1399 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve"));
1400 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve2"));
1401 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve2-aes"));
1402 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve2-sm4"));
1403 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve2-sha3"));
1404 EXPECT_TRUE(llvm::is_contained(Features, "+sve2-bitperm"));
1405}

1407TEST(TargetParserTest, AArch64ArchFeatures) {
1408 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
1409
1410 for (auto AK : AArch64::ArchKinds)
1411 EXPECT_TRUE((AK == AArch64::ArchKind::INVALID)
1412 ? !AArch64::getArchFeatures(AK, Features)
1413 : AArch64::getArchFeatures(AK, Features));
1414}

1418 {"crypto", "nocrypto", "+crypto", "-crypto"},
1419 {"flagm", "noflagm", "+flagm", "-flagm"},
1420 {"fp", "nofp", "+fp-armv8", "-fp-armv8"},
1421 {"simd", "nosimd", "+neon", "-neon"},
1422 {"fp16", "nofp16", "+fullfp16", "-fullfp16"},
1423 {"fp16fml", "nofp16fml", "+fp16fml", "-fp16fml"},
1424 {"profile", "noprofile", "+spe", "-spe"},
1425 {"ras", "noras", "+ras", "-ras"},
1426 {"lse", "nolse", "+lse", "-lse"},
1427 {"rdm", "nordm", "+rdm", "-rdm"},
1428 {"sve", "nosve", "+sve", "-sve"},
1429 {"sve2", "nosve2", "+sve2", "-sve2"},
1430 {"sve2-aes", "nosve2-aes", "+sve2-aes",
1431 "-sve2-aes"},
1432 {"sve2-sm4", "nosve2-sm4", "+sve2-sm4",
1433 "-sve2-sm4"},
1434 {"sve2-sha3", "nosve2-sha3", "+sve2-sha3",
1435 "-sve2-sha3"},
1436 {"sve2-bitperm", "nosve2-bitperm",
1437 "+sve2-bitperm", "-sve2-bitperm"},
1438 {"dotprod", "nodotprod", "+dotprod", "-dotprod"},
1439 {"rcpc", "norcpc", "+rcpc", "-rcpc" },
1440 {"rng", "norng", "+rand", "-rand"},

1443 {"pauth", "nopauth", "+pauth", "-pauth"},
1444 {"ssbs", "nossbs", "+ssbs", "-ssbs"},
1445 {"sb", "nosb", "+sb", "-sb"},
